page.title: 05 Seal Village
page.content: Seal is a village situated just outside Sevenoaks. When we visited Seal we found that the population of the village was approximately 2500. The oldest building is the church ,later we found that there was also a monastry which is now used as a block of shops. The monastry buildings are as old as the church. There are three Public Houses. One is called The Kentish Yeoman and used to be a carriage stop. It was built in 1200 AD. There are also three garages. One used to be a forge where the old horse drawn Fire Engine was kept. Under Seal village there are lots of tunnels. We found a tunnel going under the parish church which came out on the other side of the church.
